ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said paramedics were called to the scene on the corners of Beyers Naude and Juice Road, west of Johannesburg on Sunday morning. ER24 paramedics were called to the scene after a member of the public noticed the man lying on the sidewalk next to the the petrol station. Upon arrival, paramedics found the man lying on the sidewalk in a pool of blood, Meiring said. The man was assessed by ER24 paramedics and found to have sustained numerous stab wounds and showed no signs of life. Unfortunately, nothing could be done for the man and he was declared dead on the scene. Meiring said it was evident that the man had been dead for some time. He said local authorities were in the scene to investigate. Gauteng police were not immediately available for comment. African News Agency (ANA)